Definition 9. A 3-term Lie infinity algebra is a 3-term graded vector space $V=V_{0}\oplus V_{1}\oplus V_{2}$ endowed with graded antisymmetric $p$-linear maps $\ell_{p}$ of weight $p-2$, $\begin{array}[]{ll}\ell_{1}:V_{i}\to V_{i-1}&(1\leq i\leq 2),\\ \ell_{2}:V_{i}\times V_{j}\to V_{i+j}&(0\leq i+j\leq 2),\\ \ell_{3}:V_{i}\times V_{j}\times V_{k}\to V_{i+j+k+1}&(0\leq i+j+k\leq 1),\\ \ell_{4}:V_{0}\times V_{0}\times V_{0}\times V_{0}\to V_{2}\end{array}$ (all structure maps $\ell_{p}$, $p>4$, necessarily vanish), which satisfy $L_{\infty}$-condition (10) (that is trivial for all $n>5$).
